.TH vbasic 1 "Viper" "viper-vbasic" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
vbasic \- Viper BASIC interpreter and IL emitter
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B vbasic
[\fIoptions\fR] \fIFILE.bas\fR
.SH DESCRIPTION
Run Viper BASIC programs or emit IL from BASIC source. The tool wraps the \fBviper\fR front end for convenience.
.SH MODES
.TP
Run (default)
\fBvbasic\fR \fIFILE.bas\fR [run options]
.TP
Emit IL to stdout
\fBvbasic --emit-il\fR \fIFILE.bas\fR
.TP
Emit IL to file
\fBvbasic -o\fR \fIFILE.il\fR \fIFILE.bas\fR
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB- o\fR, \fB--output\fR \fIFILE\fR
Output IL file when emitting.
.TP
\fB--emit-il\fR
Emit IL instead of running.
.TP
\fB--trace\fR[=\fIil\fR|\fIsrc\fR]
Enable tracing.
.TP
\fB--bounds-checks\fR
Enable array bounds checks.
.TP
\fB--stdin-from\fR \fIFILE\fR
Redirect stdin from file.
.TP
\fB--max-steps\fR \fIN\fR
Limit instruction steps.
.TP
\fB--dump-trap\fR
Show detailed trap diagnostics.
.TP
\fB-h\fR, \fB--help\fR; \fB--version\fR
Show help or version and exit.
.SH NOTES
FUNCTIONs must return on all paths; SUBs cannot be used as expressions; array parameters are ByRef.
.SH SEE ALSO
\fBviper\fR(1), \fBilrun\fR(1)

